</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR132:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR132"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              132-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 132</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 30</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to California STEAM Robotics Day.</span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">April 21, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 132, Ochoa Bogh.
                          California STEAM Robotics Day.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would proclaim March 22, 2026, as California STEAM Robotics Day.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_49F65159-D9D7-4C7A-AB29-CC840B522B6E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, American pupils deserve access to a high-quality education in science, technology, engineering, arts, and mathematics (STEAM) for their future, California’s future, and the nation’s future; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_769D2122-2A5F-4069-A873-1D801B44B1F6"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, There is a strong need to recognize California’s STEAM leadership in technological advancement, innovation technology, and robotics because it is vital in promoting the 21st century skills of teamwork, problem solving, and technological literacy; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A2AF75BC-CF78-4230-A847-F0B7F36B8993"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Vocational education serves as an integral educational pathway, providing valuable STEAM skills in trades such as construction, automotive, information technology, and health care; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_22225FF9-D737-41EE-A9A9-6AFABF0AC167"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Career and Technical Educational (CTE) programs and the Next Generation Science Standards (NGSS) provide high quality STEAM learning, teaching industry-level topics such as the engineering design process; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F7687EAA-0D04-46ED-92EA-2C6C1D0CBF30"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Increased investments in STEAM and robotics ensure that California’s pupils have more opportunities to secure jobs in the fields of engineering, biotechnology, computer programming, artificial intelligence, animatronics, and robotics in California; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F16F638E-7077-45D2-B2F8-3F188987EBC3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Hands-on learning environments, such as makerspaces, provide pupils with access to cutting-edge tools, technology, and training that foster creativity, problem solving, and technical skill development; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_CB26A73E-41C5-425B-9B4B-105F9F84A2C6"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Immersive STEAM learning spaces are designed to engage pupils of all backgrounds, ages, and skill levels in career-focused, experiential education aligned with high-demand industries; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7FA440D2-8BC9-4C60-B7C2-2DF03143CD1A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Experiential STEAM education plays a critical role in preparing California’s pupils for careers in advanced manufacturing, engineering technology, and creative industries; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D57DEAD1-09FC-4E88-8B17-C1FCA47E8864"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, FIRST (For Inspiration and Recognition of Science and Technology) is the world’s leading youth-serving nonprofit organization advancing STEAM education; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_16235DEF-DE99-442D-9C80-101386C8F2EE"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The mission of FIRST is to motivate young people to be science and technology leaders and innovators by engaging them in exciting mentor-based programs that build science, engineering, and technology skills that inspire innovation, build confidence, and prepare young people for life; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3D905D5E-6747-4CE6-8C13-F7E1DF092B0C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The vision of FIRST is to transform our culture by creating a world where science and technology are celebrated and where pupils dream of becoming science and technology leaders; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D10E5899-C17B-40C6-ABA2-3E58737857A1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The month of March coincides with multiple robotics competitions held by FIRST; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_96B58D7E-DFCF-4C13-B55B-907900099476"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the Legislature proclaims March 22, 2026, as California STEAM Robotics Day to observe and celebrate the advancements and innovations made in California and for the pursuit of STEAM careers; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_9CC703E6-A99B-4E6A-B599-688F9B037673"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
